ThinkCERCA seeks a Chief Technology Officer to lead modernization and innovation of the ThinkCERCA core platform into a service-based, highly scalable, and ultra-performant architecture to provide the award-winning, classroom-proven ThinkCERCA framework to educators and learners across the United States. 
You will collaborate with the CEO to establish the technical vision, strategy, and delivery to achieve ThinkCERCAâ€™s mission to Spark Courageous Thinking in the minds of young learners. We are one of the few proven models in the educational technology space. Due to COVID, billions of dollars are being invested to reshape learning. Join our team and impact the future of millions of children today as part of this generational disruption. 
You will be responsible and accountable for all technology leadership decisions made at ThinkCERCA, including managing a technology budget and making investments to align the companyâ€™s technology platform with our product vision. You should be a strategic thinker, a great communicator, and an expert in technological development. 
Our ideal candidate has experience in modern development technologies like React and GraphQL as well as Ruby, Rails, and more mature frameworks. You will communicate with product, success, and engineering team members to ensure we meet customer needs through an Agile, customer-driven technology development process. You will be responsible for ThinkCERCAâ€™s platform, including authentication, authorization, structured data storage, curriculum, instruction, grading, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and more. 
You should be comfortable building a fast and reliable cloud platform to deliver a consumer quality user experience via mobile, tablet, and desktops to the regulated yet highly variable environments present in todayâ€™s US education system. 
We expect you to be well-versed in current technological trends and familiar with the impact of business models and concepts on technology decisions and product delivery. 
Responsibilities 
Leading strategy and execution for technology platforms, partnerships, external relationships, and hiring decisions to build a highly scalable learning platform with artificial intelligence and machine learning capabilities 
Oversee all system design and changes in system architecture, collaborating with senior technology resources on technical design, implementation, delivery, and quality assurance of platform features 
Acting as the technical leader and mentor across multiple teams, empowering engineers to efficient delivery of impactful features 
Leading and developing engineering team members, building a culture of individual agency, leadership and continuous improvement while serving as a role model for how software should be written 
Identifying and ensuring resolution of technical issues, and working with support teams to understand and communicate client implications 
Work with product to maintain a backlog of tools or technology enhancements that will improve the maintainability and quality of the solutions 
Encouraging teams to work collaboratively by advising and enforcing best practices with technology when needed 
Represent the technological agenda in staff meetings 
Identify, compare, select and implement technology solutions to meet current and future needs 
Develop, track and control the development of annual operating and capital budgets for purchasing, staffing and operations 
Create and maintain overall technology standards and practices, building processes to ensure adherence 
Track, analyze and monitor technology performance metrics, including disaster recovery and escalation policies in the case of failure. 
Minimum Qualifications 
Strong technical background, including 8+ years of experience with system architecture and API design and have previously been a Staff, Principal or Distinguished Engineer 
Experienced architecting and building service-oriented architectures, cloud based distributed web applications, and other systems using technologies including React, Rails, Ruby, Java, Amazon Web Services, and Heroku 
In-depth technical understanding and practical experience with at least two of the three following types of database technologies: Relational, NoSQL, or NewSQL databases 
Proven leadership skills and track record of delivering complex technical solutions in production environments on the open internet in consumer and enterprise technology 
A problem solving, growth mindset with teamwork and partnering skills for cross-group collaboration 
Preferred Qualifications: 
Strong technical background, including 10+ years of experience with system architecture and API design and have previously been a Staff, Principal or Distinguished Engineer 
Familiarity with these protocols, technologies, and practices: OAuth2, OData, GraphQL, EC2, S3, Kafka, Kubernetes 
Proficient in conducting and communicating technology strategy, evaluation, and selection processes to executive team leadership 
Experience implementing redundancy, disaster recovery and escalation plans for technology product outages and failure 
Experience implementing and supporting A/B testing, machine learning, and artificial intelligence for product improvement and innovation 
Great communication skills with proven ability to relate with both technical and business professionals 
Working knowledge of Agile Project Development Methodologies 
About ThinkCERCA 
ThinkCERCA is a top winner of the Gates Foundation Literacy Courseware Grant, and has been consistently highlighted as one of the most impactful tools in literacy. We are being used in schools across the country, and we are poised for tremendous growth based on our industry-leading growth results and award-winning platform. 
ThinkCERCA is a Chicago-based company passionately committed to improving the quality of K-12 education. Built by educators, our online platform is designed to empower teachers in personalizing literacy instruction across disciplines. The ThinkCERCA Framework provides a common language for students, teachers, parents, and administrators to drive sustainable growth in student achievement. Our work has a demonstrated impact: The results of third party studies show that schools that use ThinkCERCA see significant growth in their students' literacy and critical thinking skills. 
 
